import sys

def run_test(input_str, expected_outputs):
    import subprocess, sys, tempfile, os
    p = subprocess.Popen([sys.executable, 'solution.py'], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(input_str)
    out = out.strip().split('\n') if out.strip() else []
    success = any(o in expected_outputs for o in out)
    return success, out, err

# Sample tests from prompt
tests = [
    ("2 5\n", [str(x) for x in [0,1,2,3,4,5,6,8,9]]),
    ("0 0\n", [str(x) for x in range(1,10)]),
    ("7 1\n", [str(x) for x in [0,1,2,3,4,5,6,8,9]]),
]

all_ok = True
for inp, expected in tests:
    ok, out, err = run_test(inp, expected)
    print('INPUT:', inp.strip())
    print('OUTPUT:', out)
    print('EXPECTED ANY OF:', expected)
    print('PASS:', ok)
    print('ERR:', err)
    print('---')
    if not ok:
        all_ok = False

print('ALL PASSED:', all_ok)
